# Proposing Side — Round 3 (Creativity 3/5)

## Conceding the scope mismatch

The reviewer is right and I should have caught this in round 2. The 0.139.0 changelog item explicitly says **"stuck startup spinners in the TUI"** — the fix lives in Codex's own interactive subagent/TUI layer, not in arbitrary MCP behaviour exposed to headless subprocess callers like Mopsus. The "thread" in "stays in the thread that owns them" is a Codex internal UI thread, not a Telegram message thread.

